            <title>[KAFKA-16195] metadata.log.dir failure shouldn&apos;t shutdown broker in ZK mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16195</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ReplicaManager::handleLogDirFailure&lt;/tt&gt; shuts down the broker if the directory that has failed is the same as &lt;tt&gt;config.metadataLogDir&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/f1924353126fdf6aad2ba1f8d0c22dade59360b1/core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala#L2601&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;[0]&lt;/a&gt;. If unset, it defaults to the first log directory configured even in ZK mode.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The check should be amended to ensure the broker is either in Migration mode or Kraft mode and the broker shouldn&apos;t shut down when running in ZK mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
